ğŸŒ¿ Environment Variables in ACI
ğŸ“¦ Basic usage (with az container create)
You can pass environment variables using the --environment-variables flag, just like Docker:

Example (Bash):

az container create \
  --resource-group myResourceGroup \
  --name mycontainer2 \
  --image mcr.microsoft.com/azuredocs/aci-wordcount:latest \
  --restart-policy OnFailure \
  --environment-variables 'NumWords=5' 'MinLength=8'
  
âš ï¸ If you're using Windows CMD, use double quotes:
--environment-variables "NumWords=5" "MinLength=8"

ğŸ” Secure Environment Variables (Secrets)
For sensitive info (e.g., passwords, API keys), ACI supports secure values that:
- Donâ€™t show up in logs, CLI output, or portal
- Are only accessible inside the container

ğŸ§¾ Example YAML with both exposed and secure env vars:

apiVersion: 2018-10-01
location: eastus
name: securetest
properties:
  containers:
    - name: mycontainer
      properties:
        image: nginx
        environmentVariables:
          - name: 'NOTSECRET'
            value: 'my-exposed-value'
          - name: 'SECRET'
            secureValue: 'my-secret-value'
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 1.0
            memoryInGB: 1.5
  osType: Linux
  restartPolicy: Always
type: Microsoft.ContainerInstance/containerGroups

ğŸš€ Deploy with YAML:
az container create \
  --resource-group myResourceGroup \
  --file secure-env.yaml
